sentences: Jessica Marguerite Cleaves (December 10, 1948 â€“ May 2, 2014) was an American singer and songwriter.
Cleaves later moved to Detroit where she joined forces with George Clinton and Parliament-Funkadelic.
Cleaves later appeared on George Clinton's 1983 album Computer Games, his 1986 LP R&B Skeletons in the Closet and the P Funk All Stars' 1995 album Dope Dogs.
